[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=qpid-jms.git;h=e7692d9&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://git-wip-us.apache.org/repos/asf?p=qpid-jms.git;h=e7692d9&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPIDJMS-242&quot; title=&quot;Creation of consumer, producer or session hangs when connection is in a process of re-establishing by failover&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;QPIDJMS-242&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;QPIDJMS-242&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Creating a JMS resource can hang during failover reconnect&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;During failover the recovery attempts to recreate JMS resources that&lt;br/&gt;
were previously opened but recovers some resources that are still in the&lt;br/&gt;
process of being created lead to a double create effect on recover that&lt;br/&gt;
leads to the initial create call to hang.  Need to track state of the&lt;br/&gt;
JMS resources so that the failover recover can skip any tracked&lt;br/&gt;
instances that are either not yet opened or have already been closed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
